  "prompt": "How do I import data into MySQL from excel files?",
  "response": "Here are several methods to import data from Excel files into MySQL:\n\n1. Using MySQL Workbench:\n```sql\n-- Steps in MySQL Workbench\n1. Go to Server > Data Import\n2. Choose \"Import from Self-Contained File\"\n3. Select your Excel file\n4. Choose target schema/database\n5. Select tables and columns\n6. Start import\n```\n\n2. Using LOAD DATA INFILE (CSV method):\n```sql\n-- First, save Excel file as CSV\nLOAD DATA INFILE 'path/to/file.csv'\nINTO TABLE your_table_name\nFIELDS TERMINATED BY ','\nENCLOSED BY '\"'\nLINES TERMINATED BY '\\n'\nIGNORE 1 ROWS;  -- Skip header row if needed\n```\n\n3. Using Python (pandas):\n```python\nimport pandas as pd\nimport sqlalchemy\n\n# Read Excel file\ndf = pd.read_excel('your_file.xlsx')\n\n# Create database connection\nengine = sqlalchemy.create_engine('mysql+pymysql://username:password@localhost/database')\n\n# Import to MySQL\ndf.to_sql('table_name', engine, if_exists='replace', index=False)\n```\n\n4. Using PHP:\n```php\n<?php\n$spreadsheet = \\PhpOffice\\PhpSpreadsheet\\IOFactory::load(\"file.xlsx\");\n$worksheet = $spreadsheet->getActiveSheet();\n$data = $worksheet->toArray();\n\n// Then use PDO or mysqli to insert data\n```\n\n5. Command-line mysqlimport:\n```bash\nmysqlimport -u username -p database_name file.csv\n```\n\nKey Considerations:\n- Ensure column types match\n- Handle headers correctly\n- Clean/validate data beforehand\n- Consider large file performance\n\nRecommended Tools:\n- MySQL Workbench\n- Python pandas\n- phpMyAdmin\n- Specialized ETL tools\n\nChoose method based on:\n- File size\n- Frequency of import\n- Technical skills\n- Automation needs",
